  "texts": [
    "Once the snapshot of all layers involved in the checkpoint is complete, they can be persisted through asynchronous flushes from host to disk.",
    "However, even such an advanced asynchronous approach slows down training due to slow host memory allocation and transfers (as evaluated in Figure 12c).",
    "To mitigate this issue, we propose three optimizations.",
    "First, we pre-allocate enough host memory to hold all shards on the host memory.",
    "This pre-allocated memory will be reused for all checkpoint requests, effectively eliminating the allocation overheads for all shards, both belonging to the same and different checkpoints."
  ],
